<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="207" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="207">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="207">
The species is only known to occur in Austria. So far, its presence is confirmed from few localities, all in the Steiermark - Murtal districts: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Häuslberg">Haeuslberg</normalizedToken>
bei Leoben (type locality), Hinterberg, Kaiserberg and Gulsenberg b. Preg.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="207">
All references for Slovenia originate from the first literary source: 
<bibRefCitation author="Carnelutti, J" journalOrPublisher="Varstvo narave" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="61 - 104" refId="B6" refString="Carnelutti, J, 1992. Rdeci seznam ogrozenih metuljev (Macrolepidoptera) v Sloveniji. Varstvo narave 17: 61 - 104" title="Rdeci seznam ogrozenih metuljev (Macrolepidoptera) v Sloveniji." volume="17" year="1992">Carnelutti 1992</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, there is no record of the locality where those specimens were found and no evident material in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Carnelutti’s">Carnelutti's</normalizedToken>
collection. The first author found out about one locality where those specimens were probably collected (Mojmir Lasan, personal conversation 2012) and a visit to this locality, in Gozd Martuljek, in 2013 confirmed presence of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. santicensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santicensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">D. santicensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
population there.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="207">
Therefore, we exclude for now 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. styriaca" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styriaca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="207">D. styriaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the list of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Psychidae</taxonomicName>
from Slovenia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="207" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="207">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="207">
The genital index of males of this species after verification of old and new material from different localities, slightly differs from the previously reported values of 1.06-1.14 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Weidlich, M" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Nachrichten und Berichte" pageId="0" pageNumber="207" pagination="165 - 168" refId="B43" refString="Weidlich, M, 1996. Eine neue Psychide aus Nordungarn - Brevantennia herrmanni n. sp. (Lep., Psychidae). Entomologische Nachrichten und Berichte 40 (3): 165 - 168" title="Eine neue Psychide aus Nordungarn - Brevantennia herrmanni n. sp. (Lep., Psychidae)." volume="40" year="1996">Weidlich (1996)</bibRefCitation>
; the revised index has lower values from 0.99-1.14.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
